    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed the required gradation levels for MRL 2. Six factors are appropriately scoped as not-assessed per MRL 2 guidance for Class II devices. Validation results demonstrate NIH prediction error of 8.3% against the 15% acceptance criterion, GCI of 0.71% against the 2% criterion, and pressure-head agreement within 4.1%. The CFD model is assessed as credible for identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions within the defined COU. The decision to accept the model for regulatory submission support is confirmed.",
